[{"id":"VR000183","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of an electrolytic cell used to decompose water. The apparatus consists of 3 connected vertical cylinders and is attached to a battery. The middle cylinder is a reservoir for water. The cylinder on the left holds the cathode and collects hydrogen. The cylinder on the right holds the anode and collects oxygen. The volume of the collected hydrogen is the same as the volume of the collected oxygen. Bubbles are shown forming at both the cathode and anode. The cathode is connected by a wire to the negative terminal of the battery. The anode is connected by a wire to the positive terminal of the battery. \" height=\"358\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR000183.g02.png\" width=\"370\" /></div>\n\n<p class=\"standalone_statement style:1\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 H 2 O liquid reacts to produce 2 H 2 gas plus O 2 gas\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"2 H 2 O liquid reacts to produce 2 H 2 gas plus O 2 gas\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mn>2</mn><msub><mrow><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><mstyle><mrow><mtext>H</mtext></mrow></mstyle></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mtext>O(</mtext><mi>l</mi><mtext>)</mtext><mo>→</mo><mn>2</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><msub><mrow><mtext>H</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mtext>(</mtext><mi>g</mi><mtext>)</mtext><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mtext>O</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mtext>(</mtext><mi>g</mi><mtext>)</mtext></mrow></math></span></span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The reaction in which <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"H 2 O liquid\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"H 2 O liquid\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>H</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mtext>O</mtext><mo>(</mo><mi>l</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is decomposed into <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"H 2 gas\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"H 2 gas\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>H</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>g</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"O 2 gas\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"O 2 gas\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>O</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>g</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> is thermodynamically unfavorable (<span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta G naught is greater than 0\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"delta G naught is greater than 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>G</mi><mi>°</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>). However, an electrolytic cell, such as the one represented above, can be used to make the reaction occur. Which of the following identifies a flaw in the representation?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR000183_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Oxidation is occurring at the anode.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The equation is not correctly balanced.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Electrical energy is needed for the reaction to proceed.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The volumes of collected gas in each tube should not be the same.</p>"],"answer":3}]